<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>No more ex-soldiers will be taken to court over the 1972 Bloody Sunday shootings, Northern Ireland prosecutors announced today.</p>

<p>The Northern Ireland’s Public Prosecution Service said no further former soldiers will be prosecuted over their actions in Londonderry on January 30, when 13 civilians were fatally shot.</p>

